description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a temporary fixed term contact until 31st March 2021, for a team administrator with Community Mental Health team for Older Adults, which offer a single point of entry for all referrals to secondary mental health services for the population of Dudley.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant would be based at our Older Adults community team base at Woodside center working 37.5 hours per week at Band 3. This busy role include being the first point of contact for all telephone calls into the service and duties include processing referrals onto electronic patient record system, as well as general administration duties to support the team members and service provision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post support a variety of mental health care professionals and offers a varied range of administration duties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a self-motivated, enthusiastic person to join our current team, with a good understanding of electronic data recording systems which support patient information recording.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information regarding this post please contact Sharron Moore (Team manager) on 01384 811616.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSharron MooreJob titleTeam managerEmail addresssharron.moore@nhs.netTelephone number01384 811616&lt;/p&gt;
